    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Striker. You use powerful two-handed weapons to deal serious damage to your enemies. Your physical power and daunting presence can cause foes to cower before you, and you can temporarily increase your abilities by harnessing great bursts of terrifying rage. Depending on your choice of class features and powers, you lean toward either defender or leader as a secondary role.</p>\n<p><strong>Power Source:</strong> Primal. You are a primal champion, a warrior devoted to the natural world and an embodiment of your tribe&rsquo;s fierce traditions</p>\n<p><strong>Key Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strength</li>\n<li>Constitution</li>\n<li>Charisma</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Armour Proficiencies:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.dnd4e.equipmentPack.Item.GwsMGFG3ogxFrvmJ]{Cloth armor (basic clothing)}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.dnd4e.equipmentPack.Item.lnYMh2YvKedWTpCt]{Leather armor}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.dnd4e.equipmentPack.Item.kVD04UqK9Yx6GeRA]{Hide armor}</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Weapon Proficiencies:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd4e.srd_rules.4vItzLTePIjC1MbI]{Simple Melee Weapons}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd4e.srd_rules.oRfaQkmDSxWMx5Ln]{Military Melee Weapons}</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Bonus to Defences:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>+2 Fortitude</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level</strong><strong>: [[15]] + Con Score</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points p</strong><strong>er Level Gained: [[6]]</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Base&nbsp;</strong><strong>Healing </strong><strong>Surges per Day: [[8]] + Con Mod</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Skill Training:</strong> Choose three from the following list:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Acrobatics (Dex)</li>\n<li>Athletics (Str)</li>\n<li>Endurance (Con)</li>\n<li>Heal (Wis)</li>\n<li>Intimidate (Cha)</li>\n<li>Nature (Wis)</li>\n<li>Perception (Wis)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Class Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.dnd4e.featuresPack.Item.LEMFQnzJ3g1EPMcy]{Barbarian Agility}</li>\n<li>Rage Strike</li>\n<li>Rampage</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Choose one of the following Feral Might Features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rageblood Vigor</li>\n<li>Thaneborn Triumph</li>\n</ul>",
